This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on January 13, 2017, regarding the designation of officers or employees of the Office of Science and Technology Policy (OSTP) to act as the Director of OSTP in the event that the Director is unable to perform their duties. The memorandum outlines the order of succession for acting as the Director and includes exceptions and revocations of previous memorandums. It also includes general provisions stating that the memorandum does not affect the authority of other departments or create any enforceable rights. The memorandum concludes by authorizing its publication in the Federal Register.